1. Login into the AWS console
2. Choose the EC2 instances
3. Choose an Amazon machine image as Amazon Linux 2 AMI( 1st in the list) 
4. Leave as it is and go to the next steps
5. In add tags, add the key-value names click on configure settings
6.  Change the security group name and description to the value name that you have entered before the step. Change source to MyIP and description. Then click on Review and launch. 
7. then click on launch instances
8. Create the new key pair and download the pem file
 Then click launch instances
9. Then the instances started running
10. Click on the running instances and right-click, in that choose image and templates, in this choose to create image option in that. 
11. Enter any image name and description then click on create an image. 
12. Then go to AMI in images in the left menu, the created image is loading
13. Go to the instances and choose launch instances, that choose MyAMIs in the left menu, here it shows the image that you have created. 
14. Select that image and proceed for further steps until launch instances. 
15. I have backup the instances that I have created.

